  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to flooding in Margibi county Liberia September 2017</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam Liberia is targeting to provide an immediate lifesaving support to 1,075 household that have been reported affected by the flooding through Water Sanitation and Hygiene (WaSH) intervention as described below.  Water &#x2022; Chlorination and minor repairs of all wells with handpumps &#x2022; Refresher training of 10 Volunteers to chlorinate the water points &#x2022; Provision of 15litres/day to 1075 people for 1month + &#x2022; Procure and install temporary 4 water storage tanks at Internally Displaced Person (IDP) camps for drinking water  Sanitation &#x2022; Provision of emergency toilets to the displaced population &#x2022; Hydrated Lime treatment of the latrines  Hygiene Promotion and Protection &#x2022; Printing messages and distribution of Information, Education and Communication (IEC) materials (Oxfam has already distributed 500 Pcs of IEC materials and further printing can be done since we have an existing supplier with approved messages. &#x2022; Training 10 Volunteers on hygiene promotion (the volunteers include former Oxfam staff who already have vast knowledge in hygiene promotion) &#x2022; Procure and distribute Hygiene promotion kits &#x2022; Distribution of hand washing facilities (materials in Oxfam Liberia warehouse) &#x2022; Hygiene promotion, education including gender protection</narrative>
  </description>
